pe, Syriac missionaries were founding churches from the Mediterranean coast to Persia, converting the Turkic tribes of Central Asia, and building communities in India and China. This comprehensive work tells the underexplored story of the Syriac world over three thousand years, from its pre-Christian roots in the Aramaic tribes and the ancient Near East to its vibrant expressions in modern diaspora churches. Enhanced with beautiful images, songs, poems, and important primary source texts, this book shows the importance of Syriac history, theology, and literature in the twenty-first century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristianity and culturezSyria. 0aSyriac ChristiansxHistory. 0aSyrian churchesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh1 aDebie, Muriel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHaines, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074978640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300271256?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300271256423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300271256/original  a978-3-11-074978-6  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023